# CPA Platform — Cursor Rules
# These rules apply to every file in this project

## PYTHON RULES (apps/api)

- Always use Pydantic v2 syntax: model_config = ConfigDict(...) 
  Never use the old class Config syntax
- Use Decimal from the decimal module for ALL monetary values
  Never use float or double for any money calculation
- All functions must have complete type hints on both parameters and return values
- Use async/await throughout. No synchronous database calls in FastAPI routes
- Import order: standard library first, then third party, then local modules
- Never hardcode secrets. Always use os.environ.get("KEY_NAME")
- Every Supabase query in routers must include firm_id for tenant isolation
- Use python-dotenv load_dotenv() at the top of all entry point files
- Always handle exceptions gracefully — never let unhandled errors reach the user
- Use UUID for all primary keys, never integers

## TYPESCRIPT RULES (apps/web)

- Strict TypeScript always. Never use the "any" type under any circumstance
- Use Next.js 14 app router patterns only. Never use pages directory patterns
- Default to Server Components. Only add "use client" when the component
  needs useState, useEffect, or other browser-only React hooks
- Supabase queries in Server Components must use the server client (createServerClient)
- Supabase queries in Client Components must use the browser client (createBrowserClient)
- Never import or use the Supabase service role key in any frontend file ever
- Always handle loading and error states in components
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for all data shapes

## DATABASE RULES

- Every Supabase table must have Row Level Security enabled immediately after creation
- Every table that stores firm data must have a firm_id UUID column that is NOT NULL
- Use gen_random_uuid() for all UUID primary key defaults
- Use NUMERIC(15,2) for all money/amount columns — never FLOAT, REAL, or DOUBLE
- Every table gets created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now() 
  and updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
- Always add an index on firm_id for every table that has one
- Always add an index on client_id for every table that has one
- Foreign keys must have ON DELETE CASCADE or ON DELETE SET NULL explicitly set

## SECURITY RULES

- Never log API keys, tokens, passwords, or any secret values anywhere
- OAuth tokens must be encrypted with Fernet before storing in the database
- All user-facing API endpoints must verify the JWT token before processing
- Use hmac.compare_digest for any token comparison to prevent timing attacks
- The Supabase service role key is only used in FastAPI backend — never frontend
- All file uploads must be validated for type and size before storing

## GENERAL RULES

- Commit to git after every working feature before starting the next one
- Write the simplest code that works — no premature optimization
- If a file grows beyond 300 lines, suggest splitting it into smaller modules
- Always add error handling around external API calls (QBO, OpenAI, Supabase)
- Never expose internal error details to the frontend — log them, return generic message
